---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { siteConfig } from '../config/site';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Use" description="Basic terms for using Petera and this website.">
	<section class="article">
		<div class="shell">
			<h1>Terms of Use</h1>
			<p class="muted">Effective date: <span class="code-like">{siteConfig.effectiveDate}</span></p>

			<div class="intro-note copy">
				<p>
					These terms are meant to explain the basics of using the app and website in clear
					language. They should still be reviewed before publication.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="review-note copy" role="note">
				This page is a starter template and should be reviewed before publication.
			</div>

			<p class="copy">
				These Terms of Use govern your use of Petera and this website, provided by
				<span class="code-like">{siteConfig.ownerEntity}</span>.
			</p>

			<h2>1. Use of the app</h2>
			<p>
				Petera is provided as a reminder app intended for personal use. You agree to use the
				app and website in a lawful manner.
			</p>

			<h2>2. No guarantee of uninterrupted service</h2>
			<p>
				Petera is provided on an "as is" and "as available" basis to the extent permitted by
				applicable law. We do not promise that the app or website will always be uninterrupted,
				error-free, or suitable for every situation.
			</p>

			<h2>3. Reminder responsibility</h2>
			<p>
				Petera is a tool that helps surface reminders, but you remain responsible for your own
				decisions, deadlines, and actions.
			</p>

			<h2>4. Intellectual property</h2>
			<p>
				Unless otherwise stated, the Petera name, website content, branding, and related
				materials are owned by <span class="code-like">{siteConfig.ownerEntity}</span> or used with
				permission.
			</p>

			<h2>5. Privacy</h2>
			<p>Your use of the app and website is also subject to the Privacy Policy.</p>

			<h2>6. Changes</h2>
			<p>
				We may update these Terms from time to time. If we do, we may update the effective date
				above.
			</p>

			<h2>7. Contact</h2>
			<p>If you have questions about these Terms, contact:</p>
			<ul>
				<li><span class="code-like">{siteConfig.ownerEntity}</span></li>
				<li><span class="code-like">{siteConfig.supportEmail}</span></li>
			</ul>

			<h2>8. Jurisdiction placeholder</h2>
			<p>
				These Terms should be reviewed and adjusted for the laws and consumer-rights rules that
				apply to <span class="code-like">{siteConfig.jurisdiction}</span>.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
